### Step 2.5A–C — Candidate & Coverage Judgment

**Read candidate:** The note "12.2026-05-01.prefer-table-tests.md" claims *"Go tests should use table-driven style for repeated cases."* This is a general table-driven pattern recommendation.

**Cluster principle (recency-weighted from chunks):** Parallel Go table tests must not share the fixture map — each subtest gets its own copy; sharing caused flaky failures twice.

